Privacy Policy for Textify - Live Transcriber and Translator App
Effective date: [05/03/2023]
This Privacy Policy describes how Ugonna Oparaochaekwe ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and shares information when you use our Textify - Live Transcriber and Translator App ("Textify," "the App," or "our Service").
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully before using Textify. By using our App, you agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.
	1.	Information We Collect
In order to provide you with the best experience, we may collect the following types of information when you use Textify:
a. Audio data: We collect audio data from your device's microphone when you use our transcription and translation services.
b. Language preferences: We collect information about your language preferences, such as source and target languages, to provide accurate translations.
c. Device and usage information: We may collect information about your device, such as the device type, operating system, and other device identifiers, as well as usage information, such as app usage, access times, and session durations.
d. Payment information: If you choose to make in-app purchases, we may collect information related to the transaction, such as your name, billing address, and payment method. We do not store your full credit card details.
	2.	How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
a. Provide our Service: We use your audio data and language preferences to provide transcription and translation services.
b. Improve our Service: We analyze device and usage information to better understand how users interact with our App, identify trends and usage patterns, and make improvements to our Service.
c. Troubleshooting and support: We may use the collected information to provide technical support, address user inquiries, and resolve any issues with our Service.
d. Process payments: We use your payment information to process in-app purchases and manage your subscription, if applicable.
	3.	How We Share Your Information
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information with third parties only in the following cases:
a. Service providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers that help us provide our Service, such as transcription and translation API providers and payment processors.
b. Legal requirements: We may disclose your information if required by law, such as in response to a court order, subpoena, or other legal processes.
c. Protection of rights and interests: We may share your information to protect our rights, property, or the safety of our users or others, or to detect, prevent, or address fraud, security, or technical issues.
	4.	Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of data transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.
	5.	International Data Transfers
Your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in countries other than your country of residence, including the United States. By using our App, you consent to the transfer of your information to countries outside of your country of residence, which may have different data protection laws.
	6.	Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have certain rights concerning your personal information, such as the right to access, correct, delete, or restrict the processing of your personal information. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at ChaekweProjects@Gmail.com.
a. CCPA & CPRA: If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information we collect, disclose, and sell, as well as the right to request the deletion of your personal information. To exercise these rights, please contact us at ChaekweProjects@Gmail.com. We do not sell your personal information.
b. GDPR: If you are a resident of the European Economic Area (EEA), you have the right to access, rectify, or erase your personal data, restrict or object to the processing of your personal data, and request data portability. To exercise these rights, please contact us at ChaekweProjects@Gmail.com. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
c. CalOPPA: In accordance with the California Online Privacy Protection Act (CalOPPA), we provide you with this Privacy Policy to inform you about the categories of personal information we collect and the purposes for which we use this information.
	7.	Children's Privacy
Textify is not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information from our records.
	8.	Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the effective date at the top of this Privacy Policy. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
	9.	Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
Ugonna Oparaochaekwe
ChaekweProjects@Gmail.com
